  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n3. Regulatory Components\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Record-keeping mandates\n- Financial institution compliance obligations\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network\n- Law enforcement departments\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Regulatory compliance agencies\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Internal control mechanisms\n- Staff training programs\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes globally.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering regulations?",
